---

## What I learned

The hardest part of this product was not the ML — it was the organizational positioning. Fraud had historically been owned reactively across multiple teams with no single accountable PM. Getting the right stakeholders to agree on what "success" meant before we started building was as important as any technical decision we made.

The 120% month-over-month savings growth in the ramp period came directly from that early alignment work — because when the product launched, there was no ambiguity about who owned the outcome.

